<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Description">Description</h2>
<p>Image aliases are generated with&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://github.com/liip=
/LiipImagineBundle" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">LiipImagineBun=
dle</a>, using the underlying <a href=3D"http://imagine.readthedocs.org/en/=
latest/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Imagine library from aval=
anche123</a>.&nbsp;This bundle supports GD, Imagick or Gmagick PHP extensio=
ns, and allows you to define flexible filters in PHP.&nbsp;Image files are =
stored using the the <code style=3D"line-height: 1.42857;">IOService,</code=
> and are completely independent from <code style=3D"line-height: 1.42857;"=
>ezimage</code> Field Type. They are generated only once and cleared on dem=
and (e.g. content removal).</p>
<h2 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Configuration"><a class=3D"external-link" href=
=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/master/doc/specifica=
tions/image/image_alias_imagine.md#configuration" name=3D"user-content-conf=
iguration" rel=3D"nofollow"></a>Configuration</h2>
<p>Image variation (aka "Image alias") definition follows the same format a=
s before, in <code>ezplatform.yml</code> or any imported semantic configura=
tion file. It's <a href=3D"/display/TECHDOC/Configuration">dynamic</a>, so =
can be configured per site access and all the other scopes.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;"># Example
ezpublish:
    system:
        my_siteaccess:
            image_variations:
                small:
                    reference: null
                    filters:
                        - { name: geometry/scaledownonly, params: [100, 160=
] }
                medium:
                    reference: null
                    filters:
                        - { name: geometry/scaledownonly, params: [200, 290=
] }
                listitem:
                    reference: null
                    filters:
                        - { name: geometry/scaledownonly, params: [130, 190=
] }
                articleimage:
                    reference: null
                    filters:
                        - { name: geometry/scalewidth, params: [770] }</pre=
>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-tip=
">
<p class=3D"title">Important</p>
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-approve confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
Each variation name=20
<strong>must be unique</strong>. It may contain=20
<code>_</code> or=20
<code>-</code> or numbers, but no spaces.
</div>
</div>
<ul class=3D"task-list">
<li><p><code>reference</code>: Name of a reference variation to base the va=
riation on. If <code>null</code> (or <code>~</code>, which means <code>null=
</code> in YAML), the variation will take the original image for reference.=
 It can be any available variation configured in <code>ezpublish</code> nam=
espace, or a <code>filter_set</code> defined in <code>liip_imagine</code> n=
amespace.</p></li>
<li><p><code>filters</code>: array of filter definitions (hashes containing=
 <code>name</code> and <code>params</code> keys). See possible values below=
.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Availablefilters"><a class=3D"external-link" h=
ref=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/master/doc/specif=
ications/image/image_alias_imagine.md#available-filters" name=3D"user-conte=
nt-available-filters" rel=3D"nofollow"></a>Available filters</h3>
<p>In addition to <a href=3D"https://github.com/liip/LiipImagineBundle/blob=
/master/Resources/doc/configuration.rst" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nof=
ollow">filters exposed by LiipImagineBundle</a>, the following are availabl=
e:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<thead>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Filter name</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Parameters</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">geometry/scaledownonly</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[width, height]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Generates a thumbnail that will not exceed width=
/height.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">geometry/scalewidthdownonly</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[width]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Generates a thumbnail that will not exceed width=
.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">geometry/scaleheightdownonly</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[height]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Generates a thumbnail that will not exceed heigh=
t.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">geometry/scalewidth</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[width]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Alters image width. Proportion will be kept.</td=
>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">geometry/scaleheight</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[height]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Alters image height. Proportion will be kept.</t=
d>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">geometry/scale</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[width, height]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Alters image size, not exceeding provided width =
and height. Proportion will be kept.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">geometry/scaleexact</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[width, height]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Alters image size to fit exactly provided width =
and height. Proportion will not be kept.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">geometry/scalepercent</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[widthPercent, heightPercent]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Scales width and height with provided percent va=
lues. Proportion will not be kept.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">geometry/crop</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[width, height, startX, startY]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Crops the image. Result will have provided width=
/height, starting at provided startX/startY</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">border</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[thickBorderX, thickBorderY, color=3D#000]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Adds a border around the image. Thickness is def=
ined in px. Color is "#000" by default.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">filter/noise</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[radius=3D0]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Smooths the contours of an image (<code>imagick<=
/code>/<code>gmagick</code> only). <code>radius</code> is in pixel.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">filter/swirl</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">[degrees=3D60]</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Swirls the pixels of the center of an image (<co=
de>imagick</code>/<code>gmagick</code> only). <code>degrees</code> defaults=
 to 60=C2=B0.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">resize</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">{size: [width, height]}</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Simple resize filter (provided by LiipImagineBun=
dle).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">colorspace/gray</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">N/A</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Converts an image to grayscale.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>LiipImagineBundle supports additional settings, it is possible to combin=
e filters from the list above to <a href=3D"https://github.com/liip/LiipIma=
gineBundle/blob/master/Resources/doc/filters.rst" class=3D"external-link" r=
el=3D"nofollow">the ones provided in LiipImagineBundle</a> or custom ones.<=
/p>
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Exampleswithfilters:">Examples with filters:</=
h4>
<h5 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Withliipfilter">With liip filter</h5>
<p>For the campaign variation, it is now possible to define the <code>jpeg_=
quality</code> setting:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: css; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ezpublish:
    system:
        my_siteaccess:
            image_variations:
                reduced_jpeg:
                    reference: null
                    filters:
liip_imagine:
    driver: imagick
        filter_sets:
            mediumimage:
                jpeg_quality: 50</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h5 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Withezpublishfilter">With ezpublish filter</h5=
>
<p>Using the geometry/scalewidth filter</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: css; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ezpublish:
    system:
        my_siteaccess:
            image_variations:
                mediumimage:
                    reference: null
                    filters:
                       - geometry/scalewidth:
=09=09=09=09=09       params: [770]</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Discardedfilters">Discarded filters</h3>
<p>The following filters have been discarded due to incompatibility:</p>
<ul class=3D"task-list">
<li><code>flatten</code>. Obsolete, images are automatically flattened.</li=
>
<li><code>bordercolor</code></li>
<li><code>border/width</code></li>
<li><code>colorspace/transparent</code></li>
<li><code>colorspace</code></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Customfilters"><a class=3D"external-link" href=
=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/master/doc/specifica=
tions/image/image_alias_imagine.md#custom-filters" name=3D"user-content-cus=
tom-filters" rel=3D"nofollow"></a>Custom filters</h3>
<p>Please refer to <a href=3D"https://github.com/liip/LiipImagineBundle/blo=
b/master/Resources/doc/filters.rst#load-your-custom-filters" class=3D"exter=
nal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">LiipImagineBundle documentation on custom filter=
s</a>. <a href=3D"http://imagine.readthedocs.org/en/latest/" class=3D"exter=
nal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Imagine library documentation</a> may also be us=
eful.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Post-Processors">Post-Processors</h3>
<p><span>LiipImagineBundle supports&nbsp;</span> <a href=3D"https://github.=
com/liip/LiipImagineBundle/blob/master/Resources/doc/filters.rst#post-proce=
ssors" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">post-processors on image al=
iases</a> <span>. It is possible to specify them in image alias configurati=
on:</span></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">ezpublish:
    system:
        my_siteaccess:
            image_variations:
                articleimage:
                    reference: null
                    filters:
                        - { name: geometry/scalewidth, params: [770] }
                    post_processors:
                        jpegoptim: {}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><span> <span>Please refer to&nbsp;</span> <a href=3D"https://github.com/=
liip/LiipImagineBundle/blob/master/Resources/doc/filters.rst#post-processor=
s" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">post-processors documentation i=
n LiipImagineBundle</a> <span>&nbsp;for details.</span> </span></p>
<h3 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Drivers"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"ht=
tps://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/master/doc/specifications/=
image/image_alias_imagine.md#drivers" name=3D"user-content-drivers" rel=3D"=
nofollow"></a>Drivers</h3>
<p>LiipImagineBundle supports GD (default), Imagick and GMagick PHP extensi=
ons and only works on image blobs (no command line tool is needed). See the=
 <a href=3D"https://github.com/liip/LiipImagineBundle/blob/master/Resources=
/doc/configuration.rst" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">bundle's d=
ocumentation to learn more on that topic</a>.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Upgrade"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"ht=
tps://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/master/doc/specifications/=
image/image_alias_imagine.md#upgrade" name=3D"user-content-upgrade" rel=3D"=
nofollow"></a>Upgrade</h2>
<ul class=3D"task-list">
<li>Instantiate <code>LiipImagineBundle</code> in your kernel class</li>
</ul>
<p>If you were using ImageMagick, please install <a href=3D"http://php.net/=
imagick" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Imagick</a> or <a href=3D=
"http://php.net/gmagick" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Gmagick</=
a> PHP extensions and activate the driver in <code>liip_imagine </code>(<a =
href=3D"https://github.com/liip/LiipImagineBundle/blob/master/Resources/doc=
/configuration.rst" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">see LiipImagin=
eBundle configuration documentation for more information</a>):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;"># ezplatform.yml or config.yml
liip_imagine:
    # Driver can either "imagick", "gmagick" or "gd", depending on the PHP =
extension you're using.
    driver: imagick</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>GD will be used by default if no driver is specified.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"Imagealiashandling-Purgingaliases">Purging aliases</h2>
<p>It is possible to use the Liip Imagine console tool to clear generated a=
liases.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">$ php app/console liip:imagine:cache:remove --filters=3Dlarge
$ php app/console liip:imagine:cache:remove -v</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<p class=3D"title">Note : deleting as a group user or not owner of files</p=
>
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Due to a limitation in the Flysystem version required by eZ Platform, im=
age variations directories and files are created with a hardcoded permissio=
n that prevents group users and users other than the owner from writing or =
removing those files/directories.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>The first example will clear the image files for the&nbsp;<code>large</c=
ode> alias. The second will clear all the generated aliases (be careful), a=
nd list the removed files (<code>-v).</code></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-info=
